    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - FUEL SYSTEM - Removal - Fuel Filter Element</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Fuel Filter Element</title>
        <figure id="f2351208" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd11/D1101.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 441. Fuel filter drain lever to DRAIN</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a suitable container at end of fuel drain line to catch draining fuel. Move fuel
                filter drain lever to DRAIN.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove fuel filter element and cap assembly as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove fuel filter cap. Use an oil filter wrench if necessary.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard the bevel cut gasket and carefully clean mating surfaces.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lift fuel filter element out of housing.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
